to appear in a show at the airport opening Friday. In a statement, the New 
York-based artist said the airport administration "reflects a distrust and 
fundamental disrespect for artists." He accused the airport of going along with 
the prevailing mood of arts censorship in this country. Said airport 
commissioner Robert Cashman: "It's a quality art piece, but the timing is not 
right for it." BETH KLEID 
