<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ROLEX ROBBERY SUSPECTS SEIZED AFTER CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man suspected of snatching a Rolex watch off the wrist of another man in 
Beverly Hills on Tuesday afternoon was arrested along with an alleged 
accomplice after a five-mile car chase, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The robbery occurred in the 100 block of South Swall Drive after the victim 
left a car dealership on nearby Wilshire Boulevard, said Beverly Hills Police 
Lt. Robert Curtis. 
</P>
<P>
As the man prepared to drive off, Curtis said, one of the suspects reached into 
the vehicle and began wrenching the pricey President model Rolex from the man's 
arm. 
</P>
<P>
Residents who saw the ensuing struggle called police, then chased the suspect 
as he escaped in a waiting vehicle, Curtis said. Police eventually pulled over 
the car and the suspects -- identified by Curtis as Rex Carlton Thomas, 23, and 
Gary Hayashi, 25, both of Los Angeles -- gave up. They were to be booked on 
suspicion of robbery and other charges, Curtis said. The stolen watch and a gun 
were recovered, he said. 
</P>
