<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN THROWN OUT OF BAR DIES OF HEAD INJURIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Lawndale man who suffered massive head injuries Saturday when a bouncer 
allegedly threw him out of a Redondo Beach bar died Tuesday of his injuries at 
Harbor-UCLA Medical Center, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Alvey, 25, had fought with another patron shortly after midnight in the 
bar of Pancho and Wong's restaurant when the "door host," Eric Charles Meyer, 
intervened, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Rather than escorting Alvey out, Meyer allegedly took the man to the bar's back 
door and threw him off the deck, down four stairs and onto the asphalt, police 
said. Alvey was rushed to the hospital, where he died at 7:20 a.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Meyer, 32, of Torrance was booked Saturday at the Redondo Beach Jail on 
suspicion of attempted murder. Authorities were unavailable for comment Tuesday 
on whether the charges would be changed because of Alvey's death. 
</P>
