<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: STRAY BULLET KILLS WOMAN INSIDE PICKUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A stray bullet apparently intended for a gang member shattered the back window 
of a pickup truck and killed a woman inside as she waited for a ride home, 
authorities said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The truck owner's 5-year-old son was cut by fragments from the shattered rear 
window in the attack in the 2400 block of Ellendale Place in South-Central Los 
Angeles on Monday night, Detective Paul Mize said. 
</P>
<P>
Norma Cifuentes, 34, was sitting in the pickup as the driver warmed up the 
vehicle, Mize said. A gunman ran into the street and fired at a passing car, 
missing his target but hitting Cifuentes, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
