<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HOLLYWOOD FREEWAY LANES TO BE CLOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Department of Transportation began a three-month road rebuilding 
project Tuesday night that will require shutting down various lanes of the 
Hollywood Freeway between Chandler and Victory boulevards in North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans plans the work between 8 p.m. and 5 a.m. weekdays. After 
mid-September, the project will also involve work on the weekends. 
</P>
<P>
Also Tuesday night, Caltrans began reconstructing the median guardrail on a 
stretch of the Ventura Freeway between the Hollywood Freeway and Pass Avenue in 
Burbank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
