<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DEADLINE EXTENDED FOR $25,000 ARSON BOUNTIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors Tuesday extended the time period to 
qualify for rewards for identifying arsonists who set fires this summer in 
Glendale and the Santa Clarita Valley. 
</P>
<P>
The reward period for both fires will be extended to Oct. 1. 
</P>
<P>
The board had earlier approved $25,000 rewards for the apprehension and 
conviction of the arsonists who set the Glendale fire on June 26 and the Santa 
Clarita Valley fire on July 14. 
</P>
<P>
The Glendale blaze destroyed 46 homes and partially damaged 20 others. In the 
Santa Clarita fire, 625 acres were burned and several firefighters sustained 
minor injuries. 
</P>
