<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBERT L. BUA; CO-FOUNDED NONPROFIT AGENCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert L. Bua, chief executive officer of Bridge Focus Inc., a nonprofit 
organization with two alcohol and drug prevention and intervention centers in 
the San Fernando Valley, has died in Burbank. He was 45. 
</P>
<P>
Bua died Sunday of lymphatic cancer, said Leah Bridger, clinical services 
director of the organization. 
</P>
<P>
Born and raised in Glendale, Bua graduated from Glendale Academy in 1964 and 
began working in the youth services field. In late 1960s, he co-founded Bridge: 
A Way Across Inc., a nonprofit alcohol and drug prevention and intervention 
center in Burbank that received several Los Angeles County grants, including 
one to develop a model for community-oriented alcohol abuse prevention. 
</P>
<P>
In September, 1989, Bua's organization merged with Panorama City-based Focus 
Center for Education &amp; Development to create Bridge Focus Inc., which 
operates in Burbank and Panorama City. Bua became chief executive officer and 
president of the Bridge Focus board of directors, Bridger said. 
</P>
<P>
Bua is survived by his parents, Joseph and Stella Bua of Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service is planned for 9 a.m. Thursday at Church of the Hills at 
Forest Lawn Memorial Park-Hollywood Hills, 6300 Forest Lawn Drive. Arrangements 
were made by Forest Lawn Mortuary in Glendale. Donations can be made in Bua's 
name to Bridge Focus Inc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
