<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRAQ POSTAL NUMBERS SET UP FOR DETAINEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iraq announced Tuesday three post office box numbers where relatives and 
friends can send letters to detained foreigners. 
</P>
<P>
State-run Baghdad Radio said the "foreign guests" can receive mail via the 
"mail boxes of peace." The addresses are P.O. Box 39090, P.O. Box 50300 and 
P.O. Box 50285, all in Baghdad, Iraq. 
</P>
<P>
However, the U.S. Postal Service last week suspended service to Iraq and 
Iraqi-occupied Kuwait, citing difficulties in transportation. A postal service 
spokesman in Washington could not immediately say if or how letters sent to the 
Iraqi post office boxes could be delivered. 
</P>
