<P>
Wells Fargo to Ban Smoking: The San Francisco-based bank launched a three-phase 
program to eliminate smoking from all of its buildings and branches in 
California. 
</P>
<P>
Starting immediately, cigarette vending machines will be removed. In November, 
smoking will be permitted only in designated smoking rooms and lounges. By 
April 1, 1991, smoking will be prohibited. The program is the result of an 
employee task force. 
