<BYLINE>
<P>
By Tammerlin Drummond and Rick VanderKnyff 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW NAME: Fullerton College is modernizing its programs, so say goodby to the 
home economics division. 
</P>
<P>
Starting this year, it's the Division of Applied Design and Human Studies. . . 
. "A name change is all it is," says its dean, Karen Titus. "It was an image 
problem." . . . Over the last 2 1/2 years, courses were aimed away from home 
skills toward vocational training, and the new name reflects that, she says. 
"Women don't want to learn how to cook for their families. They want to cook 
for their own catering services." Tammerlin Drummond and Rick VanderKnyff 
</P>
</TEXT>
