<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
MEN FIGHT OFFICERS, SEE SPORTS CAR BURN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES M. GOMEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men were arrested Tuesday after they led police on a chase at speeds of up 
to 120 m.p.h. that ended in Irvine in a fight with police and the destruction 
of their sports car. 
</P>
<P>
Masaaki Tachiki, 22, and Kinichi Nikashimi, 19, both of Northridge, were 
arrested at about 1:30 a.m. Tuesday and booked into Orange County Jail on 
suspicion of evading arrest and assaulting two police officers, California 
Highway Patrol spokeswoman Officer Angel Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson said the men were spotted by two CHP officers at 1:15 a.m., speeding 
southbound along the San Diego Freeway near the Euclid Street off-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
The officers gave chase. As the car neared heavy traffic, the driver veered the 
Pontiac Trans Am sports car onto the right shoulder to pass the slower-moving 
cars. The two men got off the freeway at Irvine Center Drive, and the car spun 
out of control, Johnson said. When the officers pulled up behind the stopped 
car, the men jumped out of the Trans Am and started to fight the officers but 
were subdued, Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
Suddenly, while the four stood outside the parked cars, the Trans Am burst into 
flames.JAMES M. GOMEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
