<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRENCHMAN BUYS EMBASSY LOBELL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Embassy Lobell, winner of a heat in the Hambletonian and overall runner-up in 
the harness racing classic, has been sold to Claude Guedj of France. Previous 
owner Lou Guida said Wednesday the sale price was in seven figures. 
</P>
