<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
GILBERT LINDSAY 'DOING BETTER' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Councilman Gilbert Lindsay appeared to be "doing better" today and was 
taken off a respirator but remained hospitalized after suffering an apparent 
stroke over the weekend, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Lindsay aide Robert Gay said he expected to learn later in the day the results 
of medical tests undertaken to pinpoint Lindsay's condition. 
</P>
<P>
Lindsay, 89, left paralyzed on the right side, had been relaxing at his home 
late Sunday night when he was stricken, Gay said. 
</P>
<P>
The 9th District councilman was placed in intensive care at Daniel Freeman 
Memorial Hospital in Inglewood, where he remains. He is still unable to speak 
but is breathing on his own. 
</P>
