<P>
NO CLUES YET TO WHEREABOUTS OF 90-YEAR-OLD LAGUNA HILLS MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Sheriff's Department and the wife of a missing 90-year-old 
Laguna Hills man remained baffled today about his disappearance. 
</P>
<P>
Ted Adams, who lives in Leisure World with his 87-year-old wife, Alice, was 
last seen driving his red and white 1978 Cadillac El Dorado near the 
intersection of Alicia Parkway and Jeronimo Road at 3:45 p.m. Tuesday, 
Sheriff's Department spokesman Richard J. Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
Adams was trailing a friend driving another car when he apparently made a wrong 
turn, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
Since then, deputies have been scouring the region where he disappeared and 
have put out a missing persons bulletin to local and out-of-state agencies. 
Sheriff's investigators do not suspect foul play, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
"We've had things like this before," Olson said. "And they do show up in some 
strange places. He could have gone far and wide." 
</P>
