<P>
ACTOR PHILLIPS OUT OF HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lou Diamond Phillips of "La Bamba" and "Young Guns II" was hospitalized over 
the weekend because of bleeding from a tonsillectomy, his spokesman says. 
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old actor was taken by paramedics to Cedars-Sinai Medical Center on 
Thursday after losing blood while eating at a restaurant, Eddie Michaels said 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
"He had a tonsillectomy about two weeks ago, and this was what they call 
residual bleeding," Michaels said. "He actually lost a lot of blood. But he got 
a transfusion and is doing fine right now." 
</P>
<P>
Phillips was released from the hospital Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
