SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
BERLIN ORCHESTRA HIRES ABBADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WEST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Italian maestro Claudio Abbado has signed a seven-year contract with the Berlin 
Philharmonic, succeeding the late Herbert von Karajan. 
</P>
<P>
Abbado, 57, was picked last October by orchestra members to succeed Von 
Karajan, who died in July, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Orchestra spokesman Helge Gruenewald declined to say how much Abbado will be 
paid under the contract signed Tuesday, but the newspaper Der Tagesspiegel said 
the maestro will receive salary and benefits totaling $500,000 a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
